<section class="section-shell section-shell--accent" id="faq">
    <div class="section-heading section-heading--center">
        <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
        <h2>Spreadsheet workflow questions.</h2>
        <p>Clear expectations for the public shell today and the product direction it is preparing for.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-grid">
        <article>
            <h3>What workflows is ExcelToolStack focused on?</h3>
            <p>Formula generation, cleanup, conversion, templates, workbook QA, reporting, and spreadsheet automation for modern teams.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <h3>Is every tool live today?</h3>
            <p>No. Some pages are public positioning and static previews, while the formula copilot connects to the current formula API.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <h3>How is this different from PdfToolStack?</h3>
            <p>PdfToolStack focuses on document workflows. ExcelToolStack keeps its own spreadsheet identity while sharing a familiar ToolStack UX language.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <h3>Who is this built for?</h3>
            <p>Operations, finance, reporting, founders, analysts, and teams that repeatedly clean, explain, review, and package workbook work.</p>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="feature-band" aria-label="ExcelToolStack positioning">
    <article>
        <span>01</span>
